body:
The issue was encountered when I was working on fixing [Support pattern member assignment with data type #2328](https://github.com/verilator/verilator/issues/2328 ) and created this sample Test Case from IEEE 1800-2017 SV CH:10.9.2

The standard mentioned that "Use of the default keyword applies to members in nested structures or elements in unpacked arrays in
structures" but this is not the case as below

**Example:**
```
module top();
/* verilator lint_off UNPACKED */

  struct { // IEEE 1800-2017 SV CH:10.9.2
    int A;
    struct {
    int B, C;
    } BC1, BC2;
  } ABC, DEF;

  
  initial begin;

  DEF = '{default:10}; 
  $display("DEF.A=%d, DEF.BC1.B=%d, DEF.BC1.C=%d, DEF.BC2.B=%d, DEF.BC2.C=%d", DEF.A, DEF.BC1.B, DEF.BC1.C, DEF.BC2.B, DEF.BC2.C);

  $finish;
  end

endmodule
```

**Output:**

`DEF.A=         10, DEF.BC1.B=          0, DEF.BC1.C=         10, DEF.BC2.B=          0, DEF.BC2.C=         10`

**Error:**
_Value of 10 is not applied to DEF.BC1.B and DEF.BC2.B
They are assigned 0_

**Version:**
_git master:_ _Verilator 4.225 devel rev v4.224-49-ge0b61cea_


**Notes:**

Any information on what might be happening would be much appreciated
